<TITLE> Bay low could turn into depression </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 06 (bdnews24.com) -- The monsoon low over the north-west Bay and adjoining areas intensified into a "well-marked low" and may be brewing into a depression, the meteorological office said on Saturday. "It might be intensifying further," duty forecasting officer at the met office Sahjahan Alam told bdnews24.com. The met office, in a special bulletin, said the monsoon was moderate to strong elsewhere over the north Bay. Squally weather may affect the maritime ports and coastal areas. The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have advised to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number 3. All fishing trawlers and boats on the North Bay were asked to remain close to the coast and move cautiously until further direction.
